House Resolution 115
By: Representative Lupton of the 83rd
A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending Juana P. Alzaga; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, Juana P. Alzaga began her distinguished teaching career in 1978, establishing
3 orchestra programs at Miami Edison Middle School and High School in Miami, Florida; and
4 WHEREAS, in 1985, she joined Gwinnett County Schools and developed orchestra
5 programs at Pinckneyville Middle School, Summerour Middle School, and Norcross High
6 School; and
7 WHEREAS, she conducted the Gwinnett County Festival Orchestra from 1988 to 1994 and
8 later served as conductor of the Metropolitan Youth Symphony Orchestra, associate
9 conductor of the Emory Junior Chamber Orchestra, and a visiting orchestra director at the
10 Paideia School; and
11 WHEREAS, Juana P. Alzaga pursued advanced training as a violinist and conductor at the
12 North Carolina Conductors' Institute and the Juilliard Conductor's Institute, later becoming
13 a sought-after clinician and adjudicator for many music organizations in metro Atlanta; and
