14 WHEREAS, in April 2021, she founded the Buford Highway Orchestra Project (BHOP) as
15 a pilot program with 10 students, which has since grown to serve 55 young musicians from
16 19 DeKalb County schools; and
17 WHEREAS, the BHOP provides after-school and weekend enrichment opportunities for
18 disadvantaged students from third to eighth grade who reside in the Buford Highway
19 Corridor, giving them access to music education and fostering skills, parent involvement, and
20 community-wide engagement; and
21 WHEREAS, Juana P. Alzaga has received numerous accolades for her contributions to music
22 education, including the 2022 Georgia ASTA Lifetime Achievement Award and the 2023
23 Telemundo Community Hero Award; and
24 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that the outstanding accomplishments of this
25 remarkable and distinguished individual be appropriately recognized.
26 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
27 the members of this body recognize and commend Juana P. Alzaga for her decades of
28 contributions on behalf of the youth of this state and beyond as well as extend the most
29 sincere best wishes for continued health and happiness.
30 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
31 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to Juana
32 P. Alzaga.
